               <p>1963. <persName id="def1-1963-18390617" type="defendantName">
                     <interp inst="def1-1963-18390617" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-1963-18390617" type="age" value="14"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-1963-18390617" type="surname" value="RAYNER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-1963-18390617" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">JAMES RAYNER</hi>
                  </persName> was indicted<rs id="t18390617-1963-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18390617-1963-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18390617-1963-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="pocketpicking"></interp> for stealing, on the <rs id="t18390617-cd-212" type="crimeDate">
                        <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18390617-1963-offence-1 t18390617-cd-212"></join>22nd of May</rs>, 1 handkerchief, value 2<hi rend="italic">s</hi>., the goods of a man whose name is un<lb></lb>known, from his person.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390617-name-1350" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390617-name-1350" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390617-name-1350" type="surname" value="ARCHER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390617-name-1350" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN ARCHER</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a policeman. On the 22nd of May I was at Greenwich fair, in plain clothes. I observed the prisoner there for about a quarter of an hour, and watched him—he went behind a gentleman, lifted the tail of his coat, and took this handkerchief from it—I immediately went to the gentleman, and asked if he had lost his handkerchief—he felt, and said he had—I said, "This boy has got it; come with me, and I will take it from him"—the prisoner crept under a show—I fetched him out, took the handkerchief from him, and the gentleman claimed it—he would not come to the station-house, as he said the had so much trouble in a case before—I do not know his name.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. HORRY</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Was it this boy took it out of the pocket? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes—there were two others in company with him at one time, but he was alone when he did this—I found a quantity of toys on him, which he said a boy had put into his pocket—I asked How he came by the handkerchief—he said the boy had put that in also.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="largeCaps">
